sec.p:
For each time period p (historical vs. projected), county c, age group a, race category r, and threshold t (32.2–34.9 °C or ≥ 35 °C for EH and historical 2% heaviest rainfall amount for EP), we calculated the attributable fraction days (AFDcartp) as the product of the AFcart and the number of EH or EP days in that time period (EHDp). AFDcarp was then calculated as the sum of the two AFDcartp values, one from each threshold. For mortality and hospitalization estimates, we first calculated AFD by ZIP code z instead of county, and then we calculated AFDcarp as the weighted average of the AFDzarp in that county, where the weights were the number of cases in that ZIP code and age-race group (Additional file 1: Appendix 4). For all health outcomes, the burden-of-disease function was then defined in BenMAP as\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
